election2016 <- read_csv(Lab5_election2016_data.csv)

Question 1

glimpse(election2016)

There are 50 rows, 13 columns

This dataset is about the US election in 2016 and it takes the US population in account. It contains information regarding what state was present, an abbreviation of the state, their total vote, the vote margin, the winner of each state, what type of party each state is, the percentage point difference, what region, population percentage that lived in the metropolitan area, population percentage that is not white, estimated population in 2016, the population percentage of who has voted, and if the non white percentage of the states population is over 30. This dataset can help answer questions like who was the winner in each state, how the votes were spread out throughout the different demographics, and what candidate won in what state.
